==English==
===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[metropolitan]], from late Latin [[metropolitanus]], from 
[[Ancient Greek]] '''[[μητρόπολις]]''' "[[metropolis]]".

===Noun===
'''metro'''  (''plural'' '''[[metros]]''')

#An [[underground railway]] other than those in the US or London, in particular that in Paris.
#A train that runs on such an underground railway.
#Short for '''[[metropolitan]]'''.<!--but meaning what?-->

==== Synonyms ====
*(''underground railway''): [[el]]/[[El]] (''US''), [[subway]] (''US''), [[Tube]] (''the London underground''), [[underground]] (''UK''), [[underground railway]] (''UK'')

